headline: KeyCorp Shares Slip 9% This Month Amid Mixed Bank Earnings in 2025
summary: Trying to decide what to do with your shares of KeyCorp? You’re definitely not alone. With all the market noise this year, it’s normal for investors and curious watchers to check in on bank stocks like KeyCorp and wonder whether to buy, hold, or move on altogether. Here’s what’s been happening: KeyCorp’s stock hit a recent close of $16.96. Over the last month, shares have slipped by 9.4%, and the last seven days also saw a modest dip of 1.4%.
